date: 2026-06-11
topic: trailblazers
level: medium
---

Benjamin Franklin flew a silk kite into a Philadelphia thunderstorm today in 1752 — cedar cross-sticks, a sharp wire at the peak, hemp string running up to it, an iron key knotted where the line dropped to a dry silk ribbon he held inside a shed doorway. A knuckle to the key drew a spark. Proof that lightning was electricity, built from a kitchen drawer.
